== Births == * In the 6th year of the Keichō era (leap month) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1602]] – January 4): Tōdō Takatsugu, lord of the Tsushima Domain, was born (died 1676). * In the 12th year of the Bunsei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1829]] – December 6): Yūri Kōsei, a politician who drafted the original version of the Five-Article Oath, was born (died 1909). * In the 1st year of the Kaei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1848]] – December 6): Kawakami Sōroku, an officer in the Imperial Japanese Army, was born (died 1899). * In the 2nd year of the Kaei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1849]] – December 25): Nogi Maresuke, a general in the Imperial Japanese Army, was born (died 1912). * In the 2nd year of the Bunkyū era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1862]] – December 31): Watarase Shōzaburō, a zoologist, was born (died 1929).
== Deaths == * In the 2nd year of Emperor Saimei’s reign ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[643]] – December 30): Prince Yamase Ōe, a member of the royal family and a child of Prince Shōtoku, died. * In the 4th year of Emperor Saimei’s reign ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[658]] – December 11): Prince Arima, a child of Emperor Tenmu, died. * In the 4th year of the Teiwa era / 3rd year of the Shōhei era ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1348]] – December 2): Emperor Hanazono, the 95th Emperor of Japan, died (born 1297).
